text: Hermenegildo Leite (born May 17, 2000 in Luanda) is an Angolan sprinter. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the men's 100 metres race; his time of 11.65 seconds in the preliminary round did not qualify him for the first round. ==International competitions== {| |- !colspan="6"|Representing |- |2016 |Olympic Games |Rio de Janeiro, Brazil |(h) |100 m |11.65 |} ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Angolan male sprinters Category:Olympic athletes of Angola Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics
